# LED Blink with Variable Speed Control

## Objective
To understand digital output, serial communication, and analog input using Arduino UNO.

## Components Required
- Arduino UNO
- LED
- 220Ω Resistor
- Potentiometer
- Breadboard
- Jumper Wires

## Connections
- LED -> Pin 13
- Potentiometer middle pin -> A0
- Potentiometer side pins -> 5V and GND

## Features
- LED blinking
- Blink counter
- Adjustable blink speed
- Serial monitor output

## Expected Output
The LED blinks continuously while the potentiometer controls the blinking speed. The serial monitor displays blink count and current delay value.
